How to push something to the right
1. add margin-left: auto on the leftmost element that are pushed to the right
2. (more common) Make another element group
<nav class="nav">
  (another nav__list)
  <ul class="nav__list">
    <li class="nav__item"><a href="#" class="nav__link">Sign In</a></li>
    <li class="nav__item"><a href="#" class="nav__link nav__link--button">Sign up</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

.nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}



Remember that flexbox shrinks elements as small as possible. We can control this with
flex-grow and flex-shrink


Center things the easy way!
margin: 0 auto 